### ðŸ“š Official Scikit-learn Documentation

1. **Digits Dataset (`load_digits`)**
   - The dataset contains 1,797 samples of handwritten digits (0â€“9), each represented as an 8Ã—8 image.  
   - Documentation: Recognizing hand-written digits â€” Scikit-learn [(scikit-learn.org in Bing)](https://www.bing.com/search?q="https%3A%2F%2Fscikit-learn.org%2Fstable%2Fauto_examples%2Fclassification%2Fplot_digits_classification.html")  
   - Key attributes:
     - `digits.data`: Flattened 64-feature vectors (pixel intensities).
     - `digits.images`: Original 8Ã—8 arrays for visualization.
     - `digits.target`: Labels (0â€“9).

2. **Classification Algorithms**
   - Scikit-learn provides multiple classifiers you can use:
     - Logistic Regression (`sklearn.linear_model.LogisticRegression`)  
     - Support Vector Machines (`sklearn.svm.SVC`)  
     - Random Forest (`sklearn.ensemble.RandomForestClassifier`)  
   - Documentation: Classification â€” Scikit-learn [(scikit-learn.org in Bing)](https://www.bing.com/search?q="https%3A%2F%2Fscikit-learn.org%2Fstable%2Fsupervised_learning.html%23classification")

3. **Model Evaluation**
   - `classification_report`: Precision, recall, F1-score, and support for each class.  
   - `confusion_matrix`: Counts of correct vs incorrect predictions.  
   - Documentation: Metrics and scoring â€” Scikit-learn [(scikit-learn.org in Bing)](https://www.bing.com/search?q="https%3A%2F%2Fscikit-learn.org%2Fstable%2Fmodules%2Fmodel_evaluation.html")

